@node loading "Loading Cardz"


                             LOADING SMART CARDZ
                             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


Boot  disk  from  drive DF0:  and double click on the Smart Cardz Icon.  Cardz
requires 1Mb of memory.

@endnode

@node installing "Installing to Hard Drive"
                           INSTALLING TO HARD DRIVE
                           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

To  install Smart Cardz to your Hard Drive just drag the Smart Cards directory
to your hard disk.


@endnode

@node Bad_Pun "Playing Cardz"
                             PLAYING SMART CARDZ
                             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Smart Cardz is based around the game of Klondike.  For those of you unfamiliar
with Klondike a brief explanation of how to play the game follows.

When you first play there are seven rows of cards located along the top of the
screen.  In the first row lies one card, in the second two and so on, until in
the  last  row  there are seven.  You can only see the front side of the first
card  in  the  row.   The remainder of the cards are located in the lower left
corner  of  the  screen in what is referred to as the stock pile.  To play you
must  place  a card of one colour on a card of the other colour, you must also
follow  in  numerical  sequence e.g.  You can put a red two, on a black three.
Cards  can be taken from the stock pile or another column.  Click on the stock
pile  to  rotate  the  cards  in the stock and obtain a new card on top of the
stock.   Dependent  of  the  level  of  play the stock turns with one or three
cards.   Situated  on  the  lower right of the screen are the four ace places.
Here you may place any of the aces, followed by a two, three and so on.  Cards
placed on the ace places must be of the same suit.  Kings may be placed on any
empty  place in the upper screen.  To win the game all cards must be placed in
the correct Ace place and the rest of the screen empty.  @endnode


@node controls "Controls"
                                   CONTROLS
                                   ~~~~~~~~
To  move  cards  you  first  must  select a card by clicking on the left mouse
button  and  then  you  must click on the destination card with the left mouse
button.   To  automatically move a card to an ace place click on the card with
the right mouse button.

The card situated next to the ace stacks contains the following buttons:

	MUSIC toggles music on or off.

        NEW   restart a card game.
   
        EASY  set game to easy ( turns one card at a time ).

        HARD  set game to hard ( turns 3 cards at a time ).

        @{"LOAD" link "PD_Baby"}  load a cardz set.

        QUIT  exit game

Pressing the space bar will send Smart_cardz to the back of Workbench. 
Press Left Amiga A to bring Smart Cardz into view again.
@endnode


@node bits "General"
                                   GENERAL
                                   ~~~~~~~

*  If you make a wrong card move the source card will be de-selected.
*  Wrong choices 'Screenflash'.
*  Loading another Cardz set will restart the game.
*  It is possible to choose a lower level while playing. If you choose
   a higher level the game restarts.
*  On loading Smart Cardz searches for the cardset named "DEFAULT.CDZ", if 
   this cannot be found the program exits.
@endnode

@node PD_Baby "What's missing ?"
                                  The PD Mix
                                  ~~~~~~~~~~
This  is the PD version of Smart CardZ, and is therefore a crippled version of
the full game.
It  retains  all  the features of the full game, but is restricted in that the
load option is now more of a preview option.  You can load additional cardsets
but play time on them is limited.  After a certain number of moves a requestor
will appear and then the default cardset will be reloaded.
@endnode

@node other_sets "More Cards"
                               OTHER CARDZSETS
                              ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Smart  Cardz  uses  @{b}MODIFIED@{ub}  Klondike AGA cardsets.  These sets are converted
from  AGA  (  very  often  HAM8  )  images and reduced to 16 colours to retain
compatibility with the entire Amiga range.  Using dithering techniques quality
loss is kept to an absolute minimum.

Additional card sets will be placed in the public domain.
@endnode


